pport for demographic expansion following the Iberian colonization. The results show that during the LGM T. teniotis persisted in Mediterranean refugia and has subsequently expanded to its current circum\u2010Mediterranean range. Our findings raise questions regarding the physiological and ecological traits that enabled species with tropical affinities to survive in colder climates.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Amorim, Francisco", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Razgour, Orly", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mata, Vanessa A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lopes, Susana", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Godinho, Raquel", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ib\u00e1\u00f1ez, Carlos", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Juste, Javier", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rossiter, Stephen J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Beja, Pedro", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rebelo, Hugo", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/b380c07a1cb210cb4cff53609866e2d7", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/0e144388c555637f2d3513ec4e12bf0c9d2426e7368b820e696a16b8a289954f", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/A25BRBBG", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/A25BRBBG", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/13cc06ef29ce689bc6c63e85cffe864f!/b256662-259132", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phy